{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1054,"text":"So many of you have probably seen\nthe movie \"The Martian.\""},{"time":5141,"text":"But for those of you who did not,\nit's a movie about an astronaut"},{"time":8982,"text":"who is stranded on Mars,\nand his efforts to stay alive"},{"time":13549,"text":"until the Earth can send a rescue mission\nto bring him back to Earth."},{"time":19205,"text":"Gladly, they do re-establish communication"},{"time":22368,"text":"with the character,\nastronaut Watney, at some point"},{"time":24930,"text":"so that he's not as alone\non Mars until he can be rescued."},{"time":30726,"text":"So while you're watching the movie,\nor even if you haven't,"},{"time":33512,"text":"when you think about Mars,"},{"time":35084,"text":"you're probably thinking about\nhow far away it is and how distant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39908,"text":"And, what might not\nhave occurred to you is,"},{"time":42511,"text":"what are the logistics really like\nof working on another planet --"},{"time":46432,"text":"of living on two planets"},{"time":48702,"text":"when there are people on the Earth\nand there are rovers or people on Mars?"},{"time":54560,"text":"So think about when you have friends,\nfamilies and co-workers"},{"time":58742,"text":"in California, on the West Coast\nor in other parts of the world."},{"time":62225,"text":"When you're trying\nto communicate with them,"},{"time":64302,"text":"one of the things\nyou probably first think about is:"},{"time":66764,"text":"wait, what time is it in California?"},{"time":68884,"text":"Will I wake them up? Is it OK to call?"},{"time":71883,"text":"So even if you're interacting\nwith colleagues who are in Europe,"},{"time":75258,"text":"you're immediately thinking about:"},{"time":77324,"text":"What does it take to coordinate\ncommunication when people are far away?"},{"time":84973,"text":"So we don't have people on Mars\nright now, but we do have rovers."},{"time":90581,"text":"And actually right now, on Curiosity,\nit is 6:10 in the morning."},{"time":95710,"text":"So, 6:10 in the morning on Mars."},{"time":98876,"text":"We have four rovers on Mars."},{"time":100901,"text":"The United States has put four rovers\non Mars since the mid-1990s,"},{"time":104932,"text":"and I have been privileged enough\nto work on three of them."},{"time":108895,"text":"So, I am a spacecraft engineer,\na spacecraft operations engineer,"},{"time":113440,"text":"at NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory\nin Los Angeles, California."},{"time":118856,"text":"And these rovers\nare our robotic emissaries."},{"time":123041,"text":"So, they are our eyes and our ears,\nand they see the planet for us"},{"time":129343,"text":"until we can send people."},{"time":131200,"text":"So we learn how to operate\non other planets through these rovers."},{"time":136517,"text":"So before we send people, we send robots."},{"time":141326,"text":"So the reason there's a time difference\non Mars right now,"},{"time":145301,"text":"from the time that we're at"},{"time":146627,"text":"is because the Martian day\nis longer than the Earth day."},{"time":150954,"text":"Our Earth day is 24 hours,"},{"time":153775,"text":"because that's how long it takes\nthe Earth to rotate,"},{"time":157173,"text":"how long it takes to go around once."},{"time":159198,"text":"So our day is 24 hours."},{"time":161486,"text":"It takes Mars 24 hours and approximately\n40 minutes to rotate once."},{"time":168330,"text":"So that means that the Martian day\nis 40 minutes longer than the Earth day."},{"time":175207,"text":"So teams of people who are operating\nthe rovers on Mars, like this one,"},{"time":180386,"text":"what we are doing is we are living\non Earth, but working on Mars."},{"time":185822,"text":"So we have to think as if we are actually\non Mars with the rover."},{"time":191654,"text":"Our job, the job of this team,\nof which I'm a part of,"},{"time":195257,"text":"is to send commands to the rover\nto tell it what to do the next day."},{"time":201210,"text":"To tell it to drive or drill\nor tell her whatever she's supposed to do."},{"time":205553,"text":"So while she's sleeping --\nand the rover does sleep at night"},{"time":210043,"text":"because she needs\nto recharge her batteries"},{"time":212437,"text":"and she needs to weather\nthe cold Martian night."},{"time":216357,"text":"And so she sleeps."},{"time":217743,"text":"So while she sleeps, we work\non her program for the next day."},{"time":222857,"text":"So I work the Martian night shift."},{"time":225863,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":227478,"text":"So in order to come to work on the Earth\nat the same time every day on Mars --"},{"time":234130,"text":"like, let's say I need to be\nat work at 5:00 p.m.,"},{"time":236558,"text":"this team needs to be at work\nat 5:00 p.m. Mars time every day,"},{"time":242151,"text":"then we have to come to work\non the Earth 40 minutes later every day,"},{"time":250142,"text":"in order to stay in sync with Mars."},{"time":252345,"text":"That's like moving a time zone every day."},{"time":255321,"text":"So one day you come in at 8:00,\nthe next day 40 minutes later at 8:40,"},{"time":260800,"text":"the next day 40 minutes later at 9:20,"},{"time":264093,"text":"the next day at 10:00."},{"time":265706,"text":"So you keep moving 40 minutes every day,"},{"time":269308,"text":"until soon you're coming to work\nin the middle of the night --"},{"time":272321,"text":"the middle of the Earth night."},{"time":274162,"text":"Right? So you can imagine\nhow confusing that is."},{"time":277804,"text":"Hence, the Mars watch."},{"time":279980,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":281005,"text":"This weights in this watch\nhave been mechanically adjusted"},{"time":284547,"text":"so that it runs more slowly."},{"time":287099,"text":"Right? And we didn't start out --"},{"time":289012,"text":"I got this watch in 2004"},{"time":291262,"text":"when Spirit and Opportunity,\nthe rovers back then."},{"time":294590,"text":"We didn't start out thinking"},{"time":296220,"text":"that we were going to need Mars watches."},{"time":298675,"text":"Right? We thought, OK,\nwe'll just have the time on our computers"},{"time":303130,"text":"and on the mission control screens,\nand that would be enough."},{"time":306802,"text":"Yeah, not so much."},{"time":308207,"text":"Because we weren't just\nworking on Mars time,"},{"time":311080,"text":"we were actually living on Mars time."},{"time":314263,"text":"And we got just instantaneously confused\nabout what time it was."},{"time":318570,"text":"So you really needed something\non your wrist to tell you:"},{"time":322387,"text":"What time is it on the Earth?\nWhat time is it on Mars?"},{"time":326107,"text":"And it wasn't just the time on Mars\nthat was confusing;"},{"time":332025,"text":"we also needed to be able\nto talk to each other about it."},{"time":337337,"text":"So a \"sol\" is a Martian day --\nagain, 24 hours and 40 minutes."},{"time":342988,"text":"So when we're talking about something\nthat's happening on the Earth,"},{"time":346207,"text":"we will say, today."},{"time":348228,"text":"So, for Mars, we say, \"tosol.\""},{"time":351084,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":353992,"text":"Yesterday became \"yestersol\" for Mars."},{"time":358837,"text":"Again, we didn't start out thinking,\n\"Oh, let's invent a language.\""},{"time":363368,"text":"It was just very confusing."},{"time":364682,"text":"I remember somebody\nwalked up to me and said,"},{"time":366887,"text":"\"I would like to do this activity\non the vehicle tomorrow, on the rover.\""},{"time":370344,"text":"And I said, \"Tomorrow, tomorrow,\nor Mars, tomorrow?\""},{"time":375987,"text":"We started this terminology because\nwe needed a way to talk to each other."},{"time":381063,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":382215,"text":"Tomorrow became \"nextersol\" or \"solorrow.\""},{"time":387216,"text":"Because people have different preferences\nfor the words they use."},{"time":390855,"text":"Some of you might say \"soda\"\nand some of you might say \"pop.\""},{"time":394829,"text":"So we have people who say\n\"nextersol\" or \"solorrow.\""},{"time":398562,"text":"And then something that I noticed after\na few years of working on these missions,"},{"time":403310,"text":"was that the people who work\non the rovers, we say \"tosol.\""},{"time":408426,"text":"The people who work on the\nlanded missions that don't rove around,"},{"time":411984,"text":"they say \"tosoul.\""},{"time":413958,"text":"So I could actually tell what mission\nyou worked on from your Martian accent."},{"time":418701,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":421975,"text":"So we have the watches and the language,\nand you're detecting a theme here, right?"},{"time":425859,"text":"So that we don't get confused."},{"time":428419,"text":"But even the Earth daylight\ncould confuse us."},{"time":432669,"text":"If you think that right now,\nyou've come to work"},{"time":435032,"text":"and it's the middle of the Martian night"},{"time":437151,"text":"and there's light streaming in\nfrom the windows"},{"time":440473,"text":"that's going to be confusing as well."},{"time":443081,"text":"So you can see from\nthis image of the control room"},{"time":445610,"text":"that all of the blinds are down."},{"time":447903,"text":"So that there's no light to distract us."},{"time":450930,"text":"The blinds went down all over the building\nabout a week before landing,"},{"time":455306,"text":"and they didn't go up\nuntil we went off Mars time."},{"time":459027,"text":"So this also works\nfor the house, for at home."},{"time":462232,"text":"I've been on Mars time three times,\nand my husband is like,"},{"time":465029,"text":"OK, we're getting ready for Mars time."},{"time":466868,"text":"And so he'll put foil all over the windows\nand dark curtains and shades"},{"time":473094,"text":"because it also affects your families."},{"time":476265,"text":"And so here I was living in kind of\nthis darkened environment, but so was he."},{"time":481705,"text":"And he'd gotten used to it."},{"time":483025,"text":"But then I would get these plaintive\nemails from him when he was at work."},{"time":487257,"text":"Should I come home? Are you awake?"},{"time":490573,"text":"What time is it on Mars?"},{"time":493727,"text":"And I decided, OK,\nso he needs a Mars watch."},{"time":496249,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":497808,"text":"But of course, it's 2016,\nso there's an app for that."},{"time":502266,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":503568,"text":"So now instead of the watches,\nwe can also use our phones."},{"time":508600,"text":"But the impact on families\nwas just across the board;"},{"time":512764,"text":"it wasn't just those of us\nwho were working on the rovers"},{"time":516450,"text":"but our families as well."},{"time":518688,"text":"This is David Oh,\none of our flight directors,"},{"time":521191,"text":"and he's at the beach in Los Angeles\nwith his family at 1:00 in the morning."},{"time":525689,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":527136,"text":"So because we landed in August"},{"time":530140,"text":"and his kids didn't have to go back\nto school until September,"},{"time":534610,"text":"they actually went on to Mars time\nwith him for one month."},{"time":539382,"text":"They got up 40 minutes later every day."},{"time":544175,"text":"And they were on dad's work schedule."},{"time":546382,"text":"So they lived on Mars time for a month\nand had these great adventures,"},{"time":550381,"text":"like going bowling\nin the middle of the night"},{"time":552502,"text":"or going to the beach."},{"time":554149,"text":"And one of the things\nthat we all discovered"},{"time":557532,"text":"is you can get anywhere in Los Angeles"},{"time":561544,"text":"at 3:00 in the morning\nwhen there's no traffic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565121,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":566619,"text":"So we would get off work,"},{"time":567835,"text":"and we didn't want to go home\nand bother our families,"},{"time":570974,"text":"and we were hungry, so instead of\ngoing locally to eat something,"},{"time":574188,"text":"we'd go, \"Wait, there's this great\nall-night deli in Long Beach,"},{"time":577776,"text":"and we can get there in 10 minutes!\""},{"time":580042,"text":"So we would drive down --\nit was like the 60s, no traffic."},{"time":582787,"text":"We would drive down there,\nand the restaurant owners would go,"},{"time":586566,"text":"\"Who are you people?"},{"time":589421,"text":"And why are you at my restaurant\nat 3:00 in the morning?\""},{"time":593958,"text":"So they came to realize\nthat there were these packs of Martians,"},{"time":599661,"text":"roaming the LA freeways,\nin the middle of the night --"},{"time":605288,"text":"in the middle of the Earth night."},{"time":607335,"text":"And we did actually\nstart calling ourselves Martians."},{"time":612581,"text":"So those of us who were on Mars time\nwould refer to ourselves as Martians,"},{"time":618211,"text":"and everyone else as Earthlings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621088,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":622412,"text":"And that's because when you're moving\na time-zone every day,"},{"time":628131,"text":"you start to really feel separated\nfrom everyone else."},{"time":633968,"text":"You're literally in your own world."},{"time":638704,"text":"So I have this button on that says,\n\"I survived Mars time. Sol 0-90.\""},{"time":645653,"text":"And there's a picture of it\nup on the screen."},{"time":648422,"text":"So the reason we got these buttons\nis because we work on Mars time"},{"time":654075,"text":"in order to be as efficient as possible\nwith the rover on Mars,"},{"time":659148,"text":"to make the best use of our time."},{"time":661462,"text":"But we don't stay on Mars time\nfor more than three to four months."},{"time":665372,"text":"Eventually, we'll move to a modified Mars\ntime, which is what we're working now."},{"time":670379,"text":"And that's because it's hard on\nyour bodies, it's hard on your families."},{"time":675060,"text":"In fact, there were sleep researchers\nwho actually were studying us"},{"time":679966,"text":"because it was so unusual for humans\nto try to extend their day."},{"time":685327,"text":"And they had about 30 of us"},{"time":686641,"text":"that they would do\nsleep deprivation experiments on."},{"time":690291,"text":"So I would come in and take the test\nand I fell asleep in each one."},{"time":693878,"text":"And that was because, again,\nthis eventually becomes hard on your body."},{"time":700544,"text":"Even though it was a blast."},{"time":703883,"text":"It was a huge bonding experience\nwith the other members on the team,"},{"time":708421,"text":"but it is difficult to sustain."},{"time":712243,"text":"So these rover missions are our first\nsteps out into the solar system."},{"time":718452,"text":"We are learning how to live\non more than one planet."},{"time":723549,"text":"We are changing our perspective\nto become multi-planetary."},{"time":728943,"text":"So the next time you see\na Star Wars movie,"},{"time":731762,"text":"and there are people going\nfrom the Dagobah system to Tatooine,"},{"time":735461,"text":"think about what it really means to have\npeople spread out so far."},{"time":740975,"text":"What it means in terms\nof the distances between them,"},{"time":744061,"text":"how they will start to feel\nseparate from each other"},{"time":747905,"text":"and just the logistics of the time."},{"time":751937,"text":"We have not sent people\nto Mars yet, but we hope to."},{"time":756513,"text":"And between companies like SpaceX and NASA"},{"time":760376,"text":"and all of the international\nspace agencies of the world,"},{"time":763889,"text":"we hope to do that\nin the next few decades."},{"time":767680,"text":"So soon we will have people on Mars,\nand we truly will be multi-planetary."},{"time":774000,"text":"And the young boy or the young girl"},{"time":776436,"text":"who will be going to Mars could be\nin this audience or listening today."},{"time":784201,"text":"I have wanted to work at JPL\non these missions since I was 14 years old"},{"time":789827,"text":"and I am privileged to be a part of it."},{"time":792073,"text":"And this is a remarkable time\nin the space program,"},{"time":796151,"text":"and we are all in this journey together."},{"time":799349,"text":"So the next time you think\nyou don't have enough time in your day,"},{"time":804584,"text":"just remember, it's all a matter\nof your Earthly perspective."},{"time":809386,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":810561,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}